{"repo": "beancount/beancount", "pull_number": 1009, "instance_id": "beancount__beancount-1009", "issue_numbers": [387], "base_commit": "661d3e81476c3eba7c05576454c67698f9d8baf2", "patch": "diff --git a/beancount/tools/treeify.py b/beancount/tools/treeify.py\nindex 4d5c5b1e0..671433412 100755\n--- a/beancount/tools/treeify.py\n+++ b/beancount/tools/treeify.py\n@@ -22,7 +22,7 @@\n import sys\n \n # Default regular expressions used for splitting.\n-DEFAULT_PATTERN = r\"(Assets|Liabilities|Equity|Income|Expenses)(:[A-Z][A-Za-z0-9-_']*)*\"\n+DEFAULT_PATTERN = r\"(Assets|Liabilities|Equity|Income|Expenses)(:[A-Z0-9][A-Za-z0-9-_']*)*\"\n DEFAULT_DELIMITER = \"[ \\t]+\"\n DEFAULT_SPLITTER = \":\"\n \n", "test_patch": "diff --git a/beancount/tools/treeify_test.py b/beancount/tools/treeify_test.py\nindex b7f3b96a0..182d34036 100644\n--- a/beancount/tools/treeify_test.py\n+++ b/beancount/tools/treeify_test.py\n@@ -90,6 +90,7 @@ class TestTreeify(TestTreeifyBase):\n     def test_simple(self):\n         self.treeify_equal(\n             \"\"\"\\\n+          2014-10-19 Assets:Home:123ForestLane                    450,000.00 USD\n           2014-12-25 Assets:US:BofA:Checking                        5,545.01 USD\n           2014-11-11 Assets:US:Federal:PreTax401k\n           2014-10-04 Assets:US:Hooli:Vacation                         332.64 VACHR\n@@ -109,6 +110,8 @@ def test_simple(self):\n         \"\"\",\n             \"\"\"\\\n                      |-- Assets\n+                     |   |-- Home\n+          2014-10-19 |   |   `-- 123ForestLane                    450,000.00 USD\n                      |   `-- US\n                      |       |-- BofA\n           2014-12-25 |       |   `-- Checking                       5,545.01 USD\n", "problem_statement": "Treeify does not work with account names that start with a number\n**[Original report](https://bitbucket.org/blais/beancount/issue/387) by Megg Gawat (Bitbucket: [justmegawatt](https://bitbucket.org/justmegawatt), GitHub: [justmegawatt](https://github.com/justmegawatt)).**\n\n----------------------------------------\n\nSay I have two accounts:\n\n    2019-04-10 open Assets:Retirement:401k:CASH\n    2019-04-10 open Assets:Retirement:401k:STOCK\n\nIf I run this through Treeify it will show this:\n\n    Assets:Retirement:401k:CASH   2019-04-10  \n    Assets:Retirement:401k:STOCK  2019-04-10  \n\n\nBut if I add an \"I\" in front of the 401ks to turn them into:\n\n    2019-04-10 open Assets:Retirement:I401k:CASH\n    2019-04-10 open Assets:Retirement:I401k:STOCK\n\nit is working as intended:\n\n    `-- Assets\n        `-- Retirement\n            `-- I401k\n                |-- CASH           2019-04-10\n                `-- STOCK          2019-04-10\n\n", "hints_text": "`treeify -A` appears to be a workaround. I suspect the `DEFAULT_PATTERN` regex is just overly restrictive. I may try to PR this.\n\n", "all_hints_text": "`treeify -A` appears to be a workaround. I suspect the `DEFAULT_PATTERN` regex is just overly restrictive. I may try to PR this.\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/beancount/beancount/commit/13fc1ce6121f72c31d59d8469b9ade7ed5c7ddab"], "created_at": "2026-01-22T09:16:11Z"}
